MAN [IN VOICEOVER]:
<i>Michael.</i>

4
04:30:03,070 --> 04:30:06,005
<i>Dear Michael. Of course it's you.</i>
<i>Who else could they send?</i>

5
04:30:06,173 --> 04:30:07,504
<i>Who else could be trusted?</i>

6
04:30:07,675 --> 04:30:10,405
<i>And I know it's a long way</i>
<i>and you're ready to go to work.</i>

7
04:30:10,578 --> 04:30:13,877
<i>All I'm saying is wait, just wait, just...</i>
<i>Just please hear me out.</i>

8
04:30:14,048 --> 04:30:17,245
<i>Because this is not an episode,</i>
<i>relapse, fuckup.</i>

9
04:30:17,418 --> 04:30:19,978
<i>I'm begging you, Michael,</i>
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

10
04:30:20,154 --> 04:30:22,987
<i>Try and make believe</i>
<i>this is not just madness...</i>

11
04:30:23,157 --> 04:30:26,183
<i>... because this is not just madness.</i>

12
04:30:26,527 --> 04:30:28,791
<i>Two weeks ago,</i>
<i>I came out of the building, okay?</i>

13
04:30:28,963 --> 04:30:31,488
<i>I'm running across 6th Avenue,</i>
<i>there's a car waiting...</i>

14
04:30:31,665 --> 04:30:34,862
<i>... I got exactly 38 minutes to get</i>
<i>to the airport, and I'm dictating.</i>

15
04:30:35,035 --> 04:30:37,799
<i>There's this panicked associate</i>
<i>sprinting along beside me...</i>

16
04:30:37,972 --> 04:30:40,497
<i>... scribbling in a notepad,</i>
<i>and she starts screaming.</i>

17
04:30:40,674 --> 04:30:43,609
<i>And I realize we're standing</i>
<i>in the middle of the street...</i>

18
04:30:43,777 --> 04:30:47,770
<i>... the light's changed and there's this wall</i>
<i>of serious traffic speeding towards us.</i>

19
04:30:47,948 --> 04:30:49,973
<i>And I freeze. I can't move.</i>

20
04:30:50,150 --> 04:30:52,778
<i>I'm suddenly consumed</i>
<i>with the overwhelming sensation...</i>

21
04:30:52,953 --> 04:30:54,978
<i>... that I'm covered</i>
<i>with some sort of film.</i>

22
04:30:55,155 --> 04:30:59,751
<i>And it's in my hair, in my face.</i>
<i>And it's like a glaze, like a coating.</i>

23
04:30:59,927 --> 04:31:02,691
<i>And at first I thought,</i>
<i>"Oh, my God, I know what this is.</i>

24
04:31:02,863 --> 04:31:05,297
<i>This is some sort of amniotic,</i>
<i>embryonic fluid.</i>

25
04:31:05,466 --> 04:31:07,161
<i>I'm drenched in afterbirth.</i>

26
04:31:07,334 --> 04:31:09,996
<i>I've breached the chrysalis.</i>
<i>I've been reborn. "

27
04:31:10,170 --> 04:31:13,469
<i>But then, the traffic, the stampede,</i>
<i>the cars, the trucks, the horns...</i>

28
04:31:13,641 --> 04:31:17,668
<i>... this poor woman screaming,</i>
<i>and I'm thinking, "No. This is not rebirth.</i>

29
04:31:17,845 --> 04:31:20,712
<i>This is some kind of giddy illusion</i>
<i>of renewal...</i>

30
04:31:20,881 --> 04:31:23,645
<i>... that happens in</i>
<i>the final moment before death. "

31
04:31:23,817 --> 04:31:27,412
<i>And then I realize,</i>
<i>"No, no, no, this is completely wrong"...</i>

32
04:31:27,588 --> 04:31:30,557
<i>... because I looked back</i>
<i>at the building...</i>

33
04:31:30,724 --> 04:31:33,352
<i>... and I had the most stunning</i>
<i>moment of clarity.</i>

34
04:31:33,527 --> 04:31:35,620
<i>I realized, Michael...</i>

35
04:31:35,796 --> 04:31:39,823
<i>... that I had emerged, not through</i>
<i>the doors of Kenner, Bach & Ledeen...</i>

36
04:31:40,000 --> 04:31:43,299
<i>... not through the portals</i>
<i>of our vast and powerful law firm...</i>

37
04:31:43,470 --> 04:31:46,268
<i>... but from the asshole of an organism...</i>

38
04:31:46,440 --> 04:31:51,070
<i>... whose sole function is</i>
<i>to excrete the poison...</i>

39
04:31:51,245 --> 04:31:54,612
<i>... the ammo, the defoliant necessary</i>
<i>for other larger...</i>

40
04:31:54,782 --> 04:31:58,343
<i>... more powerful organisms</i>
<i>to destroy the miracle of humanity.</i>

41
04:31:58,519 --> 04:32:02,387
<i>And that I had been coated</i>
<i>in this patina of shit...</i>

42
04:32:02,556 --> 04:32:04,751
<i>... for the best part of my life.</i>

43
04:32:04,925 --> 04:32:08,759
<i>And the stench of it, the stain of it</i>
<i>would take the rest of my life to undo.</i>

44
04:32:08,929 --> 04:32:10,191
<i>And you know what I did?</i>

45
04:32:10,364 --> 04:32:14,095
<i>I took a deep, cleansing breath</i>
<i>and I set that notion aside. I tabled it.</i>

46
04:32:14,268 --> 04:32:18,671
<i>I said to myself, "As clear as this may be,</i>
<i>as potent a feeling as this is...</i>

47
04:32:18,839 --> 04:32:23,037
<i>... as true a thing as I believe</i>
<i>that I have witnessed today, it must wait.</i>

48
04:32:23,210 --> 04:32:25,678
<i>It must stand the test of time. "

49
04:32:25,846 --> 04:32:28,872
<i>And, Michael, the time is now.</i>

50
04:32:29,049 --> 04:32:31,279
