WOMAN [OVER PHONE]: <i>Tell me</i>
<i>about U/North, Barry. They're your clients.</i>

53
04:32:37,491 --> 04:32:41,450
<i>So you tell me why you're settling</i>
<i>a six-year-old case on the fly at midnight.</i>

54
04:32:41,628 --> 04:32:44,324
<i>Because I'm writing this story</i>
<i>whether you like it or not.</i>

55
04:32:44,498 --> 04:32:45,829
BARRY:
What does that exactly mean?

56
04:32:45,999 --> 04:32:48,399
WOMAN:
<i>Give me something I can print.</i>

57
04:32:55,409 --> 04:32:57,172
We found 97.

58
04:33:03,751 --> 04:33:06,879
I've got that cunt from
<i>The Wall Street Journal</i> on my cell phone.

59
04:33:07,054 --> 04:33:09,215
She will not go away.

60
04:33:12,693 --> 04:33:14,183
Marty Bach. How can I help you?

61
04:33:14,361 --> 04:33:17,455
WOMAN: <i>Marty, hi. It's Bridget Klein.</i>
<i>We're going with a story tomorrow...</i>

62
04:33:17,631 --> 04:33:20,862
<i>... about a settlement in the U/North</i>
<i>defoliant case. You wanna comment?</i>

63
04:33:21,034 --> 04:33:24,401
Case you're referring to is now,
as it has been for the past six years...

64
04:33:24,571 --> 04:33:26,436
...pending and unresolved.

65
04:33:26,607 --> 04:33:29,201
Till such time as our client
has their day in court...

66
04:33:29,376 --> 04:33:32,868
