Yeah, that's what my partner
kept telling me.

97
04:35:56,423 --> 04:35:57,617
DEALER:
Action's on you.

98
04:35:57,791 --> 04:35:58,780
[PHONE RINGING]

99
04:35:58,959 --> 04:36:00,756
MAN 1:
Oh, I bet the pot.

100
04:36:02,996 --> 04:36:04,827
Good to see you again.

101
04:36:33,860 --> 04:36:36,590
[PHONE RINGING]

102
04:36:37,631 --> 04:36:38,620
Hello?

103
04:36:38,799 --> 04:36:40,061
MAN: <i>Michael.</i>
- Walter.

104
04:36:40,233 --> 04:36:43,464
<i>Michael, thank God, there you are.</i>
<i>Look, I got a situation.</i>

105
04:36:43,637 --> 04:36:47,733
<i>A big problem, all right? A client of mine,</i>
<i>he just called, he hit a guy with his car.</i>

106
04:36:47,908 --> 04:36:49,808
<i>He thinks he did. He thinks he hit him.</i>

107
04:36:49,977 --> 04:36:50,966
Just now?

108
04:36:51,144 --> 04:36:53,806
<i>Yeah, just now. Ten, 15 minutes ago.</i>
<i>He's driving home.</i>

109
04:36:53,981 --> 04:36:56,040
<i>He's home now. He's there waiting.</i>

110
04:36:56,216 --> 04:36:57,376
Where?

111
04:36:57,551 --> 04:37:01,385
<i>Westchester. I'm down here in Bermuda.</i>
<i>He just got me up. I'm half asleep here.</i>

112
04:37:01,555 --> 04:37:02,579
Is he drunk?

113
04:37:02,756 --> 04:37:05,623
<i>No. It's the first thing I asked him.</i>
<i>He's good, he's sober.</i>

114
04:37:05,792 --> 04:37:07,282
Tell him to stay off the phone.

115
04:37:07,461 --> 04:37:09,725
<i>All right. But you're on it?</i>
<i>You can get up there?</i>

116
04:37:09,896 --> 04:37:11,659
<i>Because this guy, he's a huge client.</i>

117
04:37:12,232 --> 04:37:14,393
<i>This is half my book, this guy, okay?</i>

118
04:37:14,568 --> 04:37:16,001
I'm walking to the car now.

119
04:37:16,169 --> 04:37:19,536
<i>Okay. Look, look, let me call him right back</i>
<i>and I'll get the address.</i>

120
04:37:19,706 --> 04:37:23,301
<i>Just let me know you're on the way,</i>
<i>and I'll get back to you with the details.</i>

121
04:37:23,477 --> 04:37:24,910
All right. I'll be in the car.

122
04:38:18,999 --> 04:38:21,263
MAN: <i>What they did, see,</i>
<i>they changed the grade there.</i>

123
04:38:21,435 --> 04:38:23,232
They widened the street.

124
04:38:23,403 --> 04:38:26,304
I'm sure somebody told them
that that was an improvement.

125
04:38:26,473 --> 04:38:30,967
But now, you see, when it rains and when
there is fog, and with this new angle...

126
04:38:31,144 --> 04:38:34,739
...and they've got these new...
These, uh... These, uh...

127
04:38:34,915 --> 04:38:37,008
These sodium lamps, it's blinding.

128
04:38:37,184 --> 04:38:40,449
- That corner there. It is just blinding.
- They'll have to work that out.

129
04:38:40,620 --> 04:38:43,453
And it's not just tonight.
I've been saying this for years.

130
04:38:43,623 --> 04:38:48,253
I mean, how many times have we talked
about that corner? Dell?

131
04:38:48,428 --> 04:38:50,692
Mr. Greer, we don't have
a lot of time here.

132
04:38:50,864 --> 04:38:55,801
So the circumstances, the road conditions,
none of this holds any interest for you?

133
04:38:55,969 --> 04:38:58,870
What interests me is finding
the strongest criminal attorney...

134
04:38:59,039 --> 04:39:00,631
...that can be here in 15 minutes.

135
04:39:01,208 --> 04:39:04,041
Well, that sounds ominous.

136
04:39:04,211 --> 04:39:06,771
We have some good relationships
up here in Westchester.

137
04:39:06,947 --> 04:39:09,882
So, what are you? What are you?
You're not a lawyer?

138
04:39:10,050 --> 04:39:11,847
- Not the kind you need.
- What kind is that?

139
04:39:12,018 --> 04:39:13,007
A trial lawyer.

140
04:39:13,386 --> 04:39:16,048
Somebody who can see this through.
That's not what I do.

141
04:39:16,223 --> 04:39:19,784
Okay. I think we're gonna have to
pull Walter back in on this.

142
04:39:19,960 --> 04:39:22,952
I wanna get Walter back on the phone,
get him back into the mix.

143
04:39:23,130 --> 04:39:26,861
Because, I'll be frank with you,
I don't like the way this is going.

144
04:39:27,033 --> 04:39:30,696
Sir, we don't have time for Walter.
Your options are gonna get smaller quickly.

145
04:39:30,871 --> 04:39:32,930
What options?
I'm not hearing any options!

146
04:39:33,106 --> 04:39:34,334
I suggest you go local...

147
04:39:34,508 --> 04:39:37,375
...and I'm telling you there are
people here I like for this.

148
04:39:37,544 --> 04:39:39,603
Great. That's it?
That's what you got for me?

149
04:39:39,779 --> 04:39:41,804
Hey, you believe this?

150
04:39:41,982 --> 04:39:44,280
I have been a client at Kenner, Bach
for 12 years!

151
04:39:44,451 --> 04:39:48,182
You think I paid that retainer every month
for a place at the back of the line?

152
04:39:48,355 --> 04:39:51,654
Mr. Greer, you left the scene of an accident
on a slow weeknight...

153
04:39:51,825 --> 04:39:54,020
...six miles from
the state police barracks.

154
04:39:54,194 --> 04:39:56,424
If there's a line,
you're right up front.

155
04:39:56,596 --> 04:39:59,463
I can get a lawyer any time I want.
I don't need you for that.

156
04:39:59,633 --> 04:40:03,535
We're not sitting here for 45 minutes
waiting for a goddamn referral!

157
04:40:03,703 --> 04:40:05,466
I don't know what Walter
promised you...

158
04:40:05,639 --> 04:40:09,097
GREER: A miracle worker! That's Walter
on the phone, 20 minutes ago.

159
04:40:09,276 --> 04:40:12,370
Direct quote, okay? "Hang tight.
I'm sending you a miracle worker."

160
04:40:12,546 --> 04:40:14,173
- Well, he misspoke.
- About what?

161
04:40:14,347 --> 04:40:16,941
That you're the firm's fixer?
Or that you're good at it?

162
04:40:17,117 --> 04:40:18,584
Elliot.

163
04:40:18,985 --> 04:40:22,045
The guy was running! In the street!

164
04:40:22,222 --> 04:40:26,955
You take that, you add the fog,
you add the lamps, you add the angle...

165
04:40:28,461 --> 04:40:31,862
What the fuck is he doing running in
the middle of the street at midnight, huh?!

166
04:40:32,032 --> 04:40:33,329
You answer me that!

167
04:40:33,500 --> 04:40:35,297
[GLASS SHATTERS]

168
04:40:47,647 --> 04:40:50,047
What if someone had stolen the car?

169
04:40:51,651 --> 04:40:52,982
Huh?

170
04:40:53,153 --> 04:40:54,381
Happens all the time.

171
04:40:54,554 --> 04:40:56,647
Cops like hit-and-runs.

172
04:40:56,823 --> 04:40:58,848
They work them hard,
they clear them fast.

173
04:40:59,025 --> 04:41:02,222
Right now there's a B.C.I. Unit
pulling paint chips off a guard rail.

174
04:41:02,395 --> 04:41:05,728
Tomorrow, they're gonna be looking
for the owner of a custom-painted...

175
04:41:05,899 --> 04:41:08,129
...hand-rubbed Jaguar XJ-12.

176
04:41:08,301 --> 04:41:09,893
And the guy you hit?

177
04:41:10,070 --> 04:41:13,437
If he got a look at the plates,
it won't even take that long.

178
04:41:13,873 --> 04:41:15,670
[PHONE RINGING]

179
04:41:16,643 --> 04:41:18,372
There's no play here.

180
04:41:19,179 --> 04:41:21,511
There's no angle.
There's no champagne room.

181
04:41:21,681 --> 04:41:24,343
I'm not a miracle worker, I'm a janitor.

182
04:41:25,018 --> 04:41:26,576
The math on this is simple.

183
04:41:26,753 --> 04:41:29,745
The smaller the mess,
the easier it is for me to clean up.

184
04:41:30,890 --> 04:41:35,020
That's the police, isn't it?

185
04:41:35,195 --> 04:41:36,594
No.

186
04:41:37,430 --> 04:41:39,091
They don't call.

187
04:41:43,837 --> 04:41:45,202
Hello.

188
04:41:46,273 --> 04:41:48,571
Jerry, it's Michael Clayton.

189
04:41:48,742 --> 04:41:51,210
Yeah, look, I'm sorry to wake you up.

190
04:41:51,544 --> 04:41:54,274
No. I'm in the neighborhood.

191
04:41:55,215 --> 04:41:56,512
You got a pen?

192
04:45:39,005 --> 04:45:41,098
BO Y:
Mom, where's my cards?

193
04:45:46,145 --> 04:45:47,976
Where's my cards?

194
04:46:02,195 --> 04:46:03,526
Is my other deck in here?

195
04:46:03,696 --> 04:46:05,095
Did you eat?

196
04:46:05,265 --> 04:46:07,165
