197
04:46:07,333 --> 04:46:09,198
GERALD:
There were cards in our bathroom.

198
04:46:09,369 --> 04:46:10,631
Yes, I had a waffle.

199
04:46:10,803 --> 04:46:13,670
Since we're out of waffles,
I don't see how that's possible.

200
04:46:13,840 --> 04:46:15,171
It's a miracle.

201
04:46:18,645 --> 04:46:19,634
Gloves?

202
04:46:19,812 --> 04:46:20,801
[DOOR SLAMS]

203
04:46:27,287 --> 04:46:28,276
Henry!

204
04:46:33,059 --> 04:46:34,458
Come on.

205
04:46:36,462 --> 04:46:37,793
Get in.

206
04:46:40,066 --> 04:46:41,397
Got it?

207
04:46:47,240 --> 04:46:49,800
HENRY: <i>So no one's even sure</i>
<i>exactly where they are...</i>

208
04:46:49,976 --> 04:46:53,139
...because there's no borders
or landmarks or anything.

209
04:46:53,313 --> 04:46:56,043
And the town?
It's not even a town really.

210
04:46:56,215 --> 04:46:59,412
It just is this camp where all these people
have gathered to hide.

211
04:46:59,586 --> 04:47:00,575
Right.

212
04:47:00,753 --> 04:47:04,211
All these deserters and guys
that got cut off from their armies.

213
04:47:04,390 --> 04:47:07,553
All these people that are hiding
in the woods, trying to stay alive.

214
04:47:07,727 --> 04:47:09,627
