659
05:12:51,269 --> 05:12:52,361
Arthur, open the door.

660
05:12:55,940 --> 05:12:57,805
Arthur, open the door!

661
05:13:00,645 --> 05:13:03,045
Arthur, open the goddamn door!

662
05:13:04,349 --> 05:13:05,611
Arthur, op...!

663
05:13:06,417 --> 05:13:08,510
Open the fucking door!

664
05:13:14,893 --> 05:13:16,360
Arthur!

665
05:13:17,162 --> 05:13:19,790
Goddamn it, Arthur! Open the fucking...!

666
05:13:30,241 --> 05:13:31,435
Arthur!

667
05:13:42,754 --> 05:13:44,585
MAN 1: Mr. Verne, hey.
MAN 2: Hey, Danny.

668
05:13:44,756 --> 05:13:47,020
MAN 1: You guys are early.
I was pulling the other bags.

669
05:13:47,192 --> 05:13:50,059
You can put them back.
There's been a change of plans, sorry.

670
05:13:50,228 --> 05:13:52,128
MAN 3: We ready?
- Yep.

671
05:13:56,067 --> 05:13:58,331
MARTY:
Oh, for chrissake.

672
05:13:58,503 --> 05:14:00,368
Don Jeffries signed this?

673
05:14:00,838 --> 05:14:03,398
- That's really his signature?
KAREN: Mm-hm.

674
05:14:03,575 --> 05:14:05,543
Where's the original?

675
05:14:05,710 --> 05:14:10,773
We had a warehouse fire five years ago.
We lost a number of documents.

676
05:14:16,888 --> 05:14:19,755
What the hell is this doing
in Arthur's bag?

677
05:14:20,391 --> 05:14:21,915
Well, I don't know, Marty.

678
05:14:22,093 --> 05:14:26,052
That's something I was hoping
you might be able to tell me.

679
05:14:30,802 --> 05:14:32,394
BARRY:
What are we looking for?

680
05:14:32,570 --> 05:14:36,768
MARTY: If it says U/North, pull it aside.
Anything that says U/North.

681
05:14:38,243 --> 05:14:39,733
What a mess this is.

682
05:14:44,382 --> 05:14:45,610
I want all this...

683
05:14:46,551 --> 05:14:50,647
...everything here, I want it all packed up
and sent up to the house.

684
05:14:51,756 --> 05:14:53,155
Any luck, Michael?

685
05:14:53,891 --> 05:14:57,987
He booked a limo from Newark Airport at 3,
got out at West Fourth Street...

686
05:14:58,162 --> 05:15:00,130
...tipped the driver 100 bucks
and walked away.

687
05:15:00,298 --> 05:15:01,492
Did you try his apartment?

688
05:15:01,666 --> 05:15:02,826
- He moved.
- I know.

689
05:15:03,001 --> 05:15:05,367
It's a loft. No doorman.
I rang, nobody answered.

690
05:15:05,536 --> 05:15:08,198
- I called, I got the machine.
- So he could be anywhere.

691
05:15:08,373 --> 05:15:11,365
Arthur downtown is not a good idea.
Some goddamn loft.

692
05:15:11,542 --> 05:15:14,272
BARRY: Where's his daughter?
- I don't know. Spain, India.

693
05:15:14,445 --> 05:15:17,573
Mars. She's crazier than he'll ever be.

694
05:15:17,749 --> 05:15:19,580
Barry's taking over on U/North.

695
05:15:19,751 --> 05:15:21,548
We got a lot of groveling to do.

696
05:15:21,719 --> 05:15:23,812
You didn't exactly charm Karen Crowder.

697
05:15:23,988 --> 05:15:25,216
I was punting.

698
05:15:25,390 --> 05:15:28,052
You gotta saddle up here
and get things under control.

699
05:15:28,226 --> 05:15:29,215
Saddle up?

700
05:15:29,394 --> 05:15:32,454
He needs to be under a doctor's care.
He needs to be admitted.

701
05:15:32,630 --> 05:15:34,962
- Where?
MARTY: Does that really matter?

702
05:15:35,133 --> 05:15:38,034
Michael, U/North needs to know
he's under control.

703
05:15:38,202 --> 05:15:41,569
He's in a facility. They've been shook up.
They need to be reassured.

704
05:15:41,739 --> 05:15:43,934
- It's not gonna be that easy.
BARRY: Why the hell not?

705
05:15:44,108 --> 05:15:47,908
Because the laws in New York are
pretty tough on involuntary commitment.

706
05:15:48,079 --> 05:15:49,637
Did you see this fucking tape?

707
05:15:49,814 --> 05:15:52,510
I'm not arguing with you, Barry.
I'm telling you how it is.

708
05:15:52,684 --> 05:15:55,812
You know what, guys?
We got 600 lawyers in this place.

709
05:15:55,987 --> 05:15:59,479
Why don't we find out which one knows
about psychiatric-commitment statutes?

710
05:15:59,657 --> 05:16:02,319
I can tell you that right now. It's Arthur.

711
05:16:13,905 --> 05:16:15,998
IKER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>I'm at the door. We're good to go.</i>

712
05:16:17,175 --> 05:16:20,838
Yeah, roger that.
Let's keep a radio check every five, okay?

713
05:16:21,012 --> 05:16:23,173
Every five minutes, copy that.

714
05:16:49,707 --> 05:16:51,766
[PHONE RINGING]

715
05:16:57,815 --> 05:16:58,941
[MACHINE BEEPS]

716
05:16:59,117 --> 05:17:01,551
ARTHUR [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Hello, you've reached Arthur's machine.</i>

717
05:17:01,719 --> 05:17:04,187
<i>If you wish to leave a message,</i>
<i>please do so after the tone.</i>

718
05:17:04,355 --> 05:17:05,788
[MACHINE BEEPS]

719
05:17:05,957 --> 05:17:08,221
MICHAEL:
<i>Arthur, pick up the phone.</i>

720
05:17:08,393 --> 05:17:13,228
<i>Arthur, pick up the phone</i>
<i>and talk to me.</i>

721
05:17:14,632 --> 05:17:17,601
<i>No? Not gonna do it, huh?</i>

722
05:17:18,403 --> 05:17:21,497
What happened yesterday morning,
forget it. It doesn't matter.

723
05:17:21,672 --> 05:17:23,731
Someday you and I
are gonna laugh about it.

724
05:17:23,908 --> 05:17:25,375
But you gotta call me back.

725
05:17:25,543 --> 05:17:27,943
You gotta call me back soon, Arthur.

726
05:17:28,279 --> 05:17:30,213
<i>I'll tell you what.</i>

727
05:17:30,381 --> 05:17:33,248
<i>Because you said it yourself.</i>
<i>Part of this is definitely madness.</i>

728
05:17:33,418 --> 05:17:35,909
<i>And there's a chemical part to this.</i>
<i>You know it and I know it.</i>

729
05:17:36,287 --> 05:17:38,312
<i>But if you're willing to start with that...</i>

730
05:17:38,489 --> 05:17:41,617
<i>... then I'm more than willing to</i>
<i>meet you halfway and say, yes...</i>

731
05:17:41,793 --> 05:17:45,251
...this situation sucks.
This case sucks. U/North sucks.

732
05:17:45,430 --> 05:17:48,024
We can start with that.
All right, Arthur? You hear me?

733
05:17:48,199 --> 05:17:49,860
You're right about what we are.

734
05:17:50,568 --> 05:17:54,004
<i>I'm saying you're crazy. I'm saying</i>
<i>that your behavior is out of control.</i>

735
05:17:54,172 --> 05:17:55,764
<i>But I'm telling you you're right.</i>

736
05:17:55,940 --> 05:17:59,398
You called it. We're janitors, I get it.

737
05:18:01,345 --> 05:18:03,279
But we came to this, Arthur.

738
05:18:04,215 --> 05:18:07,275
<i>We made decisions.</i>
<i>It didn't happen overnight.</i>

739
05:18:07,452 --> 05:18:11,548
You can't just suddenly stop and say,
"That's it, game over. I'm into miracles."

740
05:18:12,490 --> 05:18:14,287
<i>Arthur. Come on.</i>

741
05:18:15,927 --> 05:18:18,054
Goddamn it,
pick up the phone and talk to me.

742
05:18:18,229 --> 05:18:20,561
Because whatever else
you think is so important...

743
05:18:20,731 --> 05:18:23,461
...you better let me help you,
because I'm telling you straight up...

744
05:18:23,634 --> 05:18:27,832
...janitor to janitor, I don't see
anybody else with a broom on the horizon.

745
05:18:28,005 --> 05:18:29,734
It's me, buddy. I'm the...

746
05:18:29,907 --> 05:18:30,896
[MACHINE BEEPS]

747
05:18:31,075 --> 05:18:34,602
COMPUTERIZED VOICE: <i>Mailbox is full.</i>
<i>Your message cannot be recorded.</i>

748
05:19:23,928 --> 05:19:26,055
[PHONE RINGING]

749
05:19:35,106 --> 05:19:37,574
- Hello?
ARTHUR: <i>Hello. Is Anna there?</i>

750
05:19:37,742 --> 05:19:39,107
Hang on.

751
05:19:42,513 --> 05:19:44,037
<i>Anna!</i>

752
05:19:46,050 --> 05:19:48,143
<i>Where is she? Anna!</i>

753
05:19:50,755 --> 05:19:52,450
<i>- Anna!</i>
GIRL: <i>Anna!</i>

754
05:19:53,424 --> 05:19:55,722
WOMAN:
<i>Anna, you've got a phone call!</i>

755
05:19:58,362 --> 05:20:00,455
<i>Where is she? Anna!</i>

756
05:20:11,842 --> 05:20:12,934
ANNA:
Hello?

757
05:20:13,411 --> 05:20:15,538
Anna, hi. It's Arthur.

758
05:20:15,713 --> 05:20:18,273
<i>- Hey.</i>
- Did you get some sleep?

759
05:20:18,716 --> 05:20:20,274
<i>I guess.</i>

760
05:20:20,451 --> 05:20:22,419
<i>Did you think about what we said?</i>

761
05:20:22,587 --> 05:20:25,215
- Yeah.
<i>- You didn't tell anybody, did you?</i>

762
05:20:25,389 --> 05:20:29,917
No. My sister's spying on me,
but that's normal.

763
05:20:30,094 --> 05:20:32,790
Yeah. Because I meant what I said.

764
05:20:32,964 --> 05:20:35,364
<i>I know. I know. It's just...</i>

765
05:20:36,500 --> 05:20:40,300
...there's, like, 450 people in this lawsuit.

766
05:20:41,138 --> 05:20:43,265
Why are you choosing me?

767
05:20:44,575 --> 05:20:46,941
I don't know. I'm crazy, right?

768
05:20:47,111 --> 05:20:48,669
<i>That's for sure.</i>

769
05:20:48,846 --> 05:20:50,814
I mean, does it...?
Does it really matter?

770
05:20:50,982 --> 05:20:55,146
<i>I mean, isn't it what we wait for?</i>
<i>To meet someone? And they're...</i>

771
05:20:55,319 --> 05:20:56,616
<i>They're like a lens...</i>

772
05:20:56,787 --> 05:21:00,450
...and suddenly you're looking
through them and everything changes...

773
05:21:00,625 --> 05:21:02,616
...and nothing can ever be
the same again.

774
05:21:02,793 --> 05:21:04,454
WOMAN:
<i>Who you talking to?</i>

775
05:21:04,629 --> 05:21:07,359
It's for me, okay? I get calls too.

776
05:21:07,531 --> 05:21:08,964
That guy?

777
05:21:09,133 --> 05:21:12,625
Same guy. Same guy.

778
05:21:13,270 --> 05:21:14,635
Sorry.

779
05:21:15,673 --> 05:21:19,973
No. That's... That's okay.
My mother used to listen to my calls.

780
05:21:20,144 --> 05:21:22,840
<i>She can't believe I can do anything</i>
<i>on my own.</i>

781
05:21:23,014 --> 05:21:24,481
Well, that'll change.

782
05:21:25,216 --> 05:21:26,513
ANNA:
<i>I guess.</i>

783
05:21:26,684 --> 05:21:29,710
ARTHUR: <i>Yeah, but, see,</i>
<i>that's something we can show her.</i>

784
05:21:29,887 --> 05:21:33,015
<i>That you can do something.</i>

785
05:21:33,190 --> 05:21:36,318
<i>That we could... We could do that together</i>
<i>if you want. I mean...</i>

786
05:21:36,494 --> 05:21:38,758
<i>I mean that I can help you do that.</i>

787
05:21:39,697 --> 05:21:42,325
I can get you 12 by Monday.

788
05:21:42,500 --> 05:21:44,559
Twelve's weak. Twelve looks bad.

789
05:21:44,735 --> 05:21:46,202
How do you figure that?

790
05:21:46,370 --> 05:21:49,931
They look at 75 and they look at you
and they wonder what the problem is.

791
05:21:50,107 --> 05:21:52,200
You say 12.
That's gonna make people nervous.

792
05:21:52,376 --> 05:21:55,311
This was the day before yesterday.
Let me get my ducks in order.

793
05:21:55,479 --> 05:21:56,707
What's the car worth?

794
05:21:56,881 --> 05:21:59,076
It's a lease. It's the firm's.

795
05:21:59,250 --> 05:22:03,152
So? You go to the bank.
You've got the apartment. You refinance.

796
05:22:03,320 --> 05:22:05,948
I can't. I did that three months ago.

797
05:22:06,891 --> 05:22:08,586
Are you back at the tables?

798
05:22:08,759 --> 05:22:11,694
Like I need that kind of action.
I don't have enough going on.

799
05:22:14,865 --> 05:22:16,890
I hope you're kidding.

800
05:22:17,068 --> 05:22:21,129
If he finds out you're playing cards with
his money, there's no dialogue after that.

801
05:22:22,740 --> 05:22:24,731
Do everyone a favor.

802
05:22:24,942 --> 05:22:29,345
Get out the treasure map
and start digging.

803
05:22:30,114 --> 05:22:31,604
You got a week.

804
05:22:32,950 --> 05:22:35,748
WOMAN: Hey, Michael. How are you?
MICHAEL: Hi, Cindy. I'm good.

805
05:22:35,920 --> 05:22:39,219
Come in. He's been on the phone
all morning. What else is new?

806
05:22:39,390 --> 05:22:41,415
I am trying to get him out
in 15 minutes.

807
05:22:41,592 --> 05:22:44,026
- Is he upstairs?
- He's taken over the living room.

808
05:22:44,195 --> 05:22:46,095
What are you guys doing?
Get down here.

809
05:22:46,263 --> 05:22:51,030
Soroyo, I told you to keep an eye on
these kids, make sure they're downstairs.

810
05:23:05,549 --> 05:23:07,039
MICHAEL:
Marty?

811
05:23:09,286 --> 05:23:12,153
You know what he's doing?
He's making their case.

812
05:23:12,823 --> 05:23:15,690
I'm going through his files here,
I'm reading this...

813
05:23:15,860 --> 05:23:17,725
...he's building a case against U/North.

814
05:23:17,895 --> 05:23:19,886
- Nobody's gonna let him do that.
- Let him?

815
05:23:20,064 --> 05:23:21,463
Who the hell's gonna stop him?

816
05:23:21,999 --> 05:23:24,661
You know what I just heard?
He's calling these plaintiffs.

817
05:23:24,835 --> 05:23:29,033
This woman from the deposition,
he's calling these people now.

818
05:23:29,206 --> 05:23:32,141
He's got these discovery documents.
This is a fucking nightmare.

819
05:23:32,309 --> 05:23:35,870
I tried him. Can't even leave a message.
He's got the machine jammed up.

820
05:23:36,046 --> 05:23:38,571
- Is that his briefcase?
- Yeah.

821
05:23:39,150 --> 05:23:40,947
- Why?
- We've been looking for it.

822
05:23:41,118 --> 05:23:44,645
I don't know. It came up here
with all the other stuff from his office.

823
05:23:44,822 --> 05:23:48,553
You can't believe
the crap he's got in here.

824
05:23:49,593 --> 05:23:50,617
Listen, Marty...

825
05:23:52,596 --> 05:23:54,928
...I'm in a bind here.

826
05:23:56,100 --> 05:23:58,830
I need a loan. I need 80 grand.

827
05:24:00,004 --> 05:24:02,336
- I thought you were done with that.
- It's not that.

828
05:24:02,506 --> 05:24:05,339
It's not the cards. It's none of that.
It's the restaurant.

829
05:24:05,509 --> 05:24:07,101
Eighty thousand.

830
05:24:07,278 --> 05:24:08,745
I'm sorry to jump you like this.

831
05:24:08,913 --> 05:24:11,677
I've been trying to get a meeting
with you for two weeks.

832
05:24:12,449 --> 05:24:15,748
And I know about the merger,
whether I'm supposed to or not.

833
05:24:16,153 --> 05:24:17,848
There's nothing final on the merger.

834
05:24:18,022 --> 05:24:20,957
Well, that's why I'm asking you now.
You're my meal ticket.

835
05:24:21,125 --> 05:24:23,787
Once you're out,
it's me and Barry with strangers...

836
05:24:23,961 --> 05:24:25,861
...and I'm trying to explain what I do.

837
05:24:26,030 --> 05:24:29,090
Everybody knows how valuable you are.
Everybody who needs to know.

838
05:24:29,266 --> 05:24:30,927
I'm 45 years old and I'm broke.

839
05:24:31,101 --> 05:24:33,797
I've been riding shotgun for 12 years
and I got no equity.

840
05:24:33,971 --> 05:24:35,563
I'm sorry, I don't feel reassured.

841
05:24:35,739 --> 05:24:37,764
Nobody told you to
go into the bar business.

842
05:24:37,942 --> 05:24:40,502
I only opened it so I'd have
something else, a way out.

843
05:24:40,678 --> 05:24:42,339
I had no idea you were so unhappy.

844
05:24:42,513 --> 05:24:45,539
How many times did I ask you
to put me back on a litigation team?

845
05:24:45,716 --> 05:24:47,377
- How many?
- Anybody can go to court.

846
05:24:47,551 --> 05:24:48,779
You think that's special?

847
05:24:48,953 --> 05:24:51,615
- I was good at it.
- Wonderful. So are a lot of people.

848
05:24:52,089 --> 05:24:55,456
At this, what you do, you're great.

849
05:24:55,626 --> 05:24:59,892
For chrissakes, you got something
everybody wants. You have a niche.

850
05:25:00,064 --> 05:25:03,056
You made a place.
You made a niche for yourself.

851
05:25:03,234 --> 05:25:07,295
And if it's nostalgia..."You should've seen
me when I was a DA back in Queens."

852
05:25:07,471 --> 05:25:10,872
- Let me give you a serious piece of advice:
Leave it there.

853
05:25:11,041 --> 05:25:15,034
God forbid you're not as good as
you remember. I've seen that happen too.

854
05:25:15,913 --> 05:25:18,438
But I didn't come here for advice, did I?

855
05:25:19,016 --> 05:25:22,315
So this is what? I give you the loan
or you don't help out with Arthur?

856
05:25:22,486 --> 05:25:24,078
- I never said that.
- No?

857
05:25:24,255 --> 05:25:25,586
Maybe you should have.

858
05:25:25,756 --> 05:25:30,420
I don't know how you're gonna take care
of this, but this, this is cancer.

859
05:25:30,594 --> 05:25:33,757
This is something, we don't get it
reined in and cleaned up soon...

860
05:25:33,931 --> 05:25:36,058
...everything's vulnerable. Everything.

861
05:25:36,867 --> 05:25:40,200
- What are you telling me?
- That I'm counting on you.

862
05:25:40,571 --> 05:25:44,530
I'm telling you that by this time next week,
Arthur will be under control...

863
05:25:44,708 --> 05:25:48,269
...and everybody who needs to will have
been reminded of your infinite value.

864
05:25:48,445 --> 05:25:49,742
Jesus, Marty.

865
05:25:50,014 --> 05:25:51,413
Hey.

866
05:25:51,582 --> 05:25:53,607
When did you get so fucking delicate?

867
05:25:54,718 --> 05:25:56,276
I'm late.

868
05:26:06,797 --> 05:26:09,994
[BUZZER SOUNDING]

869
05:26:35,926 --> 05:26:38,986
Why don't you just call Uncle Gene
and get the cops to help you?

870
05:26:39,163 --> 05:26:41,188
It's not that kind of a problem.

871
05:26:42,833 --> 05:26:45,233
HENRY: How much longer are we doing this?
- I don't know.

872
05:26:57,247 --> 05:27:01,047
If he comes back to get his car,
you call that number and let me know.

873
05:27:01,218 --> 05:27:04,346
- Thank you very much. I appreciate it.
- Okay. You're welcome.

874
05:27:11,729 --> 05:27:14,721
If we're not gonna get to the movie,
why don't you just say so?

875
05:27:14,898 --> 05:27:17,662
- What?
- I wanna go home.

876
05:27:17,835 --> 05:27:19,632
Come on, Henry.

877
05:27:23,040 --> 05:27:24,029
Hold up!

878
05:27:27,077 --> 05:27:28,942
Stay in the car. Lock the door.

879
05:27:30,581 --> 05:27:33,550
- Arthur! Arthur!
ARTHUR: Oh!

880
05:27:33,717 --> 05:27:35,048
Wait up.

881
05:27:35,886 --> 05:27:39,287
Michael. Jeez. You scared me.

882
05:27:40,691 --> 05:27:43,421
- Making a delivery?
- No, no, no.

883
05:27:44,261 --> 05:27:46,889
Very funny. No, nothing like that.

884
05:27:47,064 --> 05:27:50,659
Here, take one, please. Really.
