05:44:07,914 --> 05:44:09,711
But when you see him like that...

1112
05:44:09,883 --> 05:44:12,647
...you don't have to worry.
That's not how it'll be for you.

1113
05:44:12,819 --> 05:44:15,379
You're not gonna be someone
that goes through life...

1114
05:44:15,555 --> 05:44:19,150
...wondering why shit keeps
falling out of the sky around them.

1115
05:44:19,325 --> 05:44:21,725
I know that. I know it.

1116
05:44:21,895 --> 05:44:23,192
Okay?

1117
05:44:27,434 --> 05:44:31,598
I see it every time I look at you.
I see it right now.

1118
05:44:33,907 --> 05:44:36,637
I don't know where you got it from,
but you got it.

1119
05:44:38,344 --> 05:44:39,675
Okay?

1120
05:44:43,650 --> 05:44:45,481
[PHONE RINGING]

1121
05:44:52,892 --> 05:44:54,189
Hello?

1122
05:45:04,204 --> 05:45:08,106
The neighbors came by.
They're renovating the loft downstairs.

1123
05:45:08,274 --> 05:45:12,904
They had water flooding from
his bathroom down to their place.

1124
05:45:13,246 --> 05:45:18,548
His front door, fire escape,
he had everything locked up pretty good.

1125
05:45:18,718 --> 05:45:23,052
It took our guys 10 minutes.
They had to knock the thing down.

1126
05:45:24,057 --> 05:45:26,992
There's pills all over the place.

1127
05:45:27,794 --> 05:45:32,857
Just the scene alone is
pretty definitive for suicide.

1128
05:45:33,566 --> 05:45:35,966
Then I spoke to some of your partners...

1129
05:45:36,135 --> 05:45:39,730
...who ran down these problems
he'd been having lately, so...

1130
05:45:42,075 --> 05:45:45,238
- Is there a note?
- No. They looked.

1131
05:45:45,812 --> 05:45:50,374
It could be an accident or he was gonna
write a note and just messed up.

1132
05:45:51,451 --> 05:45:52,748
Can I get in there?

1133
05:45:52,919 --> 05:45:55,945
His place? Not now. It's sealed.

1134
05:45:56,656 --> 05:46:00,820
Once the seal goes up, it's frozen.
We're gonna try and reach his daughter.

1135
05:46:00,994 --> 05:46:04,122
I guess she's off in Europe.
But she's gotta come in.

1136
05:46:04,764 --> 05:46:07,824
Or the M.E.'s gotta come back
with a toxicology report.

1137
05:46:08,001 --> 05:46:11,698
That's a couple of weeks at least
that it's gotta stay like that.

1138
05:46:12,138 --> 05:46:13,503
Sorry.

1139
05:46:15,542 --> 05:46:17,009
Sure.

1140
05:46:23,283 --> 05:46:24,272
Okay.

1141
05:46:28,521 --> 05:46:33,117
I know your brother a little.
My wife works the 190 out in Queens.

1142
05:46:34,761 --> 05:46:35,921
I'll tell him hello.

1143
05:46:36,095 --> 05:46:38,120
If something comes in,
I'll get back to you.

1144
05:46:38,998 --> 05:46:40,363
Yeah. I appreciate it.

1145
05:46:40,533 --> 05:46:42,330
I'm sorry for your loss.

1146
05:47:00,820 --> 05:47:03,414
- Michael.
- Jeff.

1147
05:47:03,590 --> 05:47:05,057
This is tough.

1148
05:47:05,224 --> 05:47:06,816
Yeah, it is. He in here?

1149
05:47:18,371 --> 05:47:20,566
Dumb son of a bitch.

1150
05:47:21,074 --> 05:47:22,200
What a thing.

1151
05:47:22,375 --> 05:47:24,605
BARRY: Hold on.
- I don't even know...

1152
05:47:24,777 --> 05:47:26,677
- I'm so sorry.
- Yeah. All right.

1153
05:47:26,846 --> 05:47:30,077
I didn't even get a chance to talk to him.

1154
05:47:30,249 --> 05:47:33,707
That crazy goddamn bastard.

1155
05:47:34,253 --> 05:47:37,245
What a waste.
What the hell was he thinking?

1156
05:47:37,924 --> 05:47:39,755
Marty? I gotta set this up.

1157
05:47:39,926 --> 05:47:41,450
Go. Go.

1158
05:47:42,195 --> 05:47:43,526
You okay?

1159
05:47:44,263 --> 05:47:46,026
Yeah, I'm fine.

1160
05:47:47,300 --> 05:47:49,359
Come on, let's get you a drink.

1161
05:47:52,205 --> 05:47:56,437
I just keep replaying all this back.
Like, did I push him too hard?

1162
05:47:56,609 --> 05:47:57,837
Not a chance.

1163
05:47:58,011 --> 05:47:59,808
I just couldn't get through to him.

1164
05:47:59,979 --> 05:48:03,142
What, you scared him to death?
Come on. The man was a bull.

1165
05:48:03,616 --> 05:48:07,245
- Never happened.
- Why does he fold, then? Why does he?

1166
05:48:09,288 --> 05:48:11,153
It's gotta be an accident.

1167
05:48:11,324 --> 05:48:12,882
No, no. Arthur without a note?

1168
05:48:13,059 --> 05:48:16,028
He couldn't piss without leaving a memo.
Has to be an accident.

1169
05:48:16,195 --> 05:48:18,459
I don't get that.
I don't understand that either.

1170
05:48:18,631 --> 05:48:20,861
One minute he's gonna
take on the whole world...

1171
05:48:21,034 --> 05:48:24,060
...and then 12 hours later,
he's sucking down pills. Why?

1172
05:48:24,237 --> 05:48:25,636
Why?

1173
05:48:27,073 --> 05:48:31,567
Because people are
fucking incomprehensible. "Why?"

1174
05:48:34,147 --> 05:48:37,605
Thirty years I know Arthur.

1175
05:48:38,084 --> 05:48:39,745
Good years.

1176
05:48:41,287 --> 05:48:45,451
And what I feel right now, if I'm honest?

1177
05:48:48,294 --> 05:48:50,785
I can't even say, it's so awful.

1178
05:48:51,931 --> 05:48:53,592
You can say it.

1179
05:48:56,135 --> 05:48:58,035
We caught a lucky break.

1180
05:49:01,040 --> 05:49:03,338
We did, didn't we?

1181
05:49:08,047 --> 05:49:11,483
Marty? We need to get up to the office.

1182
05:49:11,651 --> 05:49:13,380
MARTY: They accepted?
BARRY: In principle.

1183
05:49:13,553 --> 05:49:16,386
Don Jeffries wants us
on the phone in half an hour.

1184
05:49:16,556 --> 05:49:19,457
I tried to explain about Arthur,
but they're short on sympathy.

1185
05:49:19,625 --> 05:49:21,525
Wait a minute. U/North is settling?

1186
05:49:21,694 --> 05:49:25,755
BARRY: They see a window. They wanna try.
It's their show. What are we gonna do?

1187
05:49:27,500 --> 05:49:30,628
You did what you could, Michael.
We all did.

1188
05:49:32,038 --> 05:49:33,369
It's...

1189
05:49:33,539 --> 05:49:35,200
It's what we got.

1190
05:49:36,342 --> 05:49:39,175
- You need a ride?
- No, thanks, I'm fine.

1191
05:49:55,828 --> 05:49:58,319
[PHONE RINGING]

1192
05:50:11,978 --> 05:50:12,967
Hello.

1193
05:50:13,146 --> 05:50:15,740
Hello. Hi. I'm looking for Anna Kysersun.

1194
05:50:15,915 --> 05:50:17,007
WOMAN:
<i>Who is this?</i>

1195
05:50:17,183 --> 05:50:20,675
Michael Clayton. I'm an attorney in
New York. I got your number from Arthur.

1196
05:50:20,853 --> 05:50:23,720
<i>- You have got some nerve.</i>
- Excuse me?

1197
05:50:23,890 --> 05:50:27,690
You get her all the way to New York City
and then leave her at the airport?

1198
05:50:28,094 --> 05:50:29,686
<i>This is not a complicated person.</i>

1199
05:50:29,862 --> 05:50:32,695
<i>This is a girl who's never been</i>
<i>farther than Milwaukee.</i>

1200
05:50:32,865 --> 05:50:34,856
- Wait a minute. Now, wait.
<i>- No, you wait.</i>

1201
05:50:35,034 --> 05:50:39,266
She's coming home tomorrow
and when she does, if you call here again...

1202
05:50:39,438 --> 05:50:41,736
Are you telling me she's
in New York right now?

1203
05:50:42,208 --> 05:50:44,199
<i>This is a young girl, do you hear me?</i>

1204
05:50:44,377 --> 05:50:46,811
MICHAEL:
She's in the city right now?

1205
05:50:46,979 --> 05:50:48,537
<i>What kind of people are you?</i>

1206
05:50:48,714 --> 05:50:51,740
MICHAEL: Listen. You just stay
on the phone one second. One second.

1207
05:51:23,015 --> 05:51:24,346
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1208
05:51:24,517 --> 05:51:26,382
MICHAEL:
<i>Anna.</i>

1209
05:51:28,087 --> 05:51:29,577
Anna?

1210
05:51:30,389 --> 05:51:33,358
My name's Michael Clayton.
I'm a friend of Arthur's.

1211
05:51:33,526 --> 05:51:36,188
I spoke with your sister.
She told me you were here.

1212
05:51:37,496 --> 05:51:39,361
Please open the door, Anna.

1213
05:51:42,435 --> 05:51:44,027
[CLICKS]

1214
05:51:50,676 --> 05:51:52,371
What are you thinking?

1215
05:51:53,179 --> 05:51:58,481
I don't know. I'll watch the door.
You check his car. Let's get some details.

1216
05:52:01,320 --> 05:52:04,585
He didn't want to say
exactly what it was.

1217
05:52:06,459 --> 05:52:10,293
Just that when I got here,
he would pick me up...

1218
05:52:10,463 --> 05:52:12,829
...and show me, and I would see...

1219
05:52:13,799 --> 05:52:16,666
...that it was something
that would win the whole case.

1220
05:52:19,872 --> 05:52:21,737
Even this morning...

1221
05:52:21,908 --> 05:52:23,500
...I mean, I thought:

1222
05:52:25,044 --> 05:52:29,708
"Okay, if I get to the airport
and the ticket's not there, then I'll know.

1223
05:52:29,882 --> 05:52:34,979
Okay, you're stupid,
and you can go home now."

1224
05:52:37,590 --> 05:52:42,425
But it was there and he paid
like 800 dollars...

1225
05:52:42,595 --> 05:52:45,257
...for a first-class ticket.

1226
05:52:45,431 --> 05:52:46,898
And I just...

1227
05:52:50,836 --> 05:52:52,770
I got on the plane.

1228
05:52:55,541 --> 05:52:57,475
I believed him.

1229
05:53:02,248 --> 05:53:06,912
You think maybe he was
in some way disappointed?

1230
05:53:07,753 --> 05:53:11,746
Let's say that he knew that you
told somebody else about all of this...

1231
05:53:11,924 --> 05:53:15,360
...and, I don't know, in some crazy way,
he was disappointed by that?

1232
05:53:16,462 --> 05:53:19,363
- But I didn't.
- You must have told somebody else.

1233
05:53:19,532 --> 05:53:21,090
No.

1234
05:53:22,268 --> 05:53:24,429
He made me promise.

1235
05:53:25,938 --> 05:53:30,307
You didn't tell anybody else about this?
Not one other person?

1236
05:53:31,444 --> 05:53:32,843
No.

1237
05:53:37,616 --> 05:53:40,551
He really was crazy, wasn't he?

1238
05:53:53,299 --> 05:53:56,166
- You talking about this?
- Let me see.

1239
05:53:57,670 --> 05:53:59,331
- You know what that is?
- Yeah.

1240
05:54:00,272 --> 05:54:03,332
You said a favor.
That's more than a favor.

1241
05:54:03,509 --> 05:54:05,670
Well, nobody's gonna know
where it came from.

1242
05:54:07,046 --> 05:54:09,480
- Are you that jammed up?
- What are you talking about?

1243
05:54:09,648 --> 05:54:12,276
Who asked for this?
It's the restaurant, right?

1244
05:54:12,451 --> 05:54:14,942
One of these guys you owe?
"Get me a seal."

1245
05:54:15,121 --> 05:54:16,748
You really wanna know?

1246
05:55:34,066 --> 05:55:36,296
This just gets better and better.

1247
05:55:37,937 --> 05:55:39,529
What are we doing?

1248
05:57:41,193 --> 05:57:42,217
MAN:
Freeze!

1249
05:57:42,394 --> 05:57:45,124
Right there, asshole! Don't move!

1250
05:57:45,297 --> 05:57:47,561
- It's all right, I'm a friend!
- Get your hands up!

1251
05:57:47,733 --> 05:57:50,258
Get your hands up now! Now!

1252
05:57:50,436 --> 05:57:52,370
- What's in your hand?
- It's a book.

1253
05:57:52,538 --> 05:57:55,405
Drop it! Drop it, now! Drop it!

1254
05:57:55,574 --> 05:57:58,873
WOMAN: Turn around. Slowly.
- All right. All right. Okay.

1255
05:57:59,044 --> 05:58:00,875
WOMAN: Who else is here?
MICHAEL: Nobody.

1256
05:58:01,046 --> 05:58:03,480
WOMAN: I said, who else is here?
MICHAEL: Nobody's here!

1257
05:58:03,649 --> 05:58:05,048
Check in there.

1258
05:58:05,851 --> 05:58:09,150
You move, I'll take your head off.

1259
05:58:39,018 --> 05:58:43,455
Now I owe this scumbag and his wife...
Who's a complete piece of shit in my unit.

1260
05:58:43,622 --> 05:58:45,715
- Now I owe them both my balls.
MICHAEL: I'm sorry.

1261
05:58:45,891 --> 05:58:47,882
- You know I am.
- "Nobody will know it's me."

1262
05:58:48,060 --> 05:58:51,120
You know what happens they don't
bury this, that I gave you this?

1263
05:58:51,297 --> 05:58:52,662
It's bad. I know it.

1264
05:58:52,831 --> 05:58:55,891
I'm 18 months away from my 20.
You just put my pension in jeopardy.

1265
05:58:56,068 --> 05:58:58,036
- You made your point.
- It's not a point!

1266
05:58:58,203 --> 05:59:00,569
- Who called 911?
- What?

1267
05:59:00,873 --> 05:59:03,808
The building was empty. I was quiet.
I wasn't there very long.

1268
05:59:03,976 --> 05:59:06,410
Who called it in?
Does that make sense to you...?

1269
05:59:06,578 --> 05:59:08,136
This never happened.

1270
05:59:09,448 --> 05:59:11,473
You got these cops thinking
you're a lawyer.

1271
05:59:11,650 --> 05:59:13,709
You got these lawyers thinking
you're a cop.

1272
05:59:13,886 --> 05:59:18,016
You got everybody fooled, don't you?
Everybody but you.

1273
05:59:18,190 --> 05:59:20,283
You know exactly what you are.

1274
05:59:33,906 --> 05:59:35,430
We tried calling you six times.

1275
05:59:35,607 --> 05:59:37,734
But your machine must be
busted or something.

1276
05:59:39,578 --> 05:59:41,068
We gave it our best shot.

1277
05:59:42,414 --> 05:59:44,905
We ran out of red covers.
We only had 2000 in stock...

1278
05:59:45,084 --> 05:59:46,949
...so we did the other thousand in blue.

1279
06:00:08,374 --> 06:00:09,864
Is everything all right?

1280
06:00:10,042 --> 06:00:11,270
It's fine, yeah.

1281
06:00:11,977 --> 06:00:15,037
You have a van or something?
Because I have 25 boxes back there...

1282
06:00:15,214 --> 06:00:18,274
Do me a favor. Hang on to them.

1283
06:00:18,450 --> 06:00:20,680
I'll come back and pick everything up
next week.

1284
06:00:20,853 --> 06:00:22,912
- Seriously? Thanks, man.
- Yeah.

1285
06:00:43,475 --> 06:00:44,840
Hello.

1286
06:00:49,915 --> 06:00:53,214
Don. You go ahead. I'll catch up to you.

1287
06:00:53,786 --> 06:00:55,083
What?

1288
06:01:02,494 --> 06:01:04,655
VERNE:
<i>Do you know Michael Clayton?</i>

1289
06:01:04,830 --> 06:01:06,320
KAREN:
<i>Yeah, why?</i>

1290
06:01:06,498 --> 06:01:08,261
We have a situation.

1291
06:01:28,053 --> 06:01:29,611
Hey, did they find you?

1292
06:01:29,788 --> 06:01:32,814
- Who?
- Marty. I don't think they've gone in yet.

1293
06:01:40,999 --> 06:01:42,330
Marty.

1294
06:01:42,668 --> 06:01:45,865
Your phone's off. There's too much
going on for your phone to be off.

1295
06:01:46,038 --> 06:01:48,029
- I need a minute.
- Yeah, well, we're late...

1296
06:01:48,207 --> 06:01:49,834
We never got to finish last night.

1297
06:01:50,008 --> 06:01:52,135
Did you close the place?
You look like hell.

1298
06:01:52,311 --> 06:01:55,371
- No, I left right after you left.
- Lf you say so.

1299
06:01:55,547 --> 06:01:58,243
We've been here all night.
We had to make an announcement.

1300
06:01:58,417 --> 06:02:01,682
Jean! I need the thing, the envelope.

1301
06:02:01,854 --> 06:02:05,051
I wanted your input. I couldn't get you.
I had to pull the trigger.

1302
06:02:05,224 --> 06:02:08,159
I put Bob Nast and Kim,
probably a mistake.

1303
06:02:08,327 --> 06:02:11,660
They're gonna pull together a memorial
service by the end of the week.

1304
06:02:11,830 --> 06:02:14,094
I told them to call you
if they need any help.

1305
06:02:14,600 --> 06:02:17,364
No, no, no.
The other one. The other one.

1306
06:02:17,936 --> 06:02:20,234
So we cut you a check this morning.

1307
06:02:20,405 --> 06:02:23,704
There's some strings attached.
And Barry...

1308
06:02:23,876 --> 06:02:28,006
There's no way around this,
Barry's gonna have to be involved.

1309
06:02:31,783 --> 06:02:34,217
What if Arthur was on to something?

1310
06:02:34,386 --> 06:02:36,047
What do you mean? On to what?

1311
06:02:36,221 --> 06:02:39,088
U/North. What if he wasn't crazy?
What if he was right?

1312
06:02:39,258 --> 06:02:41,419
Right about what?
That we're on the wrong side?

1313
06:02:41,593 --> 06:02:44,027
Wrong side, wrong way,
everything, all of it.

1314
06:02:44,196 --> 06:02:47,131
This is news?
This case reeked from day one.

1315
06:02:47,299 --> 06:02:49,290
I gotta tell you how we pay the rent?

1316
06:02:49,468 --> 06:02:52,198
What would they do?
What would they do if he went public?

1317
06:02:52,371 --> 06:02:55,772
What would they do? Are you fucking soft?
They're doing it.

1318
06:02:55,941 --> 06:02:58,375
We don't straighten the settlement out
in 24 hours...

1319
06:02:58,544 --> 06:03:00,603
...they're gonna withhold
$9 million in fees.

1320
06:03:00,779 --> 06:03:03,748
Then they'll pull out the video of Arthur
doing his flashdance.

1321
06:03:03,916 --> 06:03:05,645
They'll sue us for legal malpractice.

1322
06:03:05,817 --> 06:03:09,480
Except there won't be anything to win
because the London merger will be dead...

1323
06:03:09,655 --> 06:03:12,317
...and we'll be selling off
the goddamn furniture.

1324
06:03:12,791 --> 06:03:14,486
That's 80.

1325
06:03:14,993 --> 06:03:16,790
We're calling it a bonus.

1326
06:03:17,629 --> 06:03:19,654
Three-year contract
at your current numbers.

1327
06:03:19,831 --> 06:03:21,458
That's assuming this all works out.

1328
06:03:21,633 --> 06:03:22,793
You're doing this now?

1329
06:03:24,469 --> 06:03:27,802
Look, I agreed to this, okay?
But there's rules now.

1330
06:03:27,973 --> 06:03:30,840
You want the contract,
you sign a confidentiality agreement.

1331
06:03:31,009 --> 06:03:33,102
It's gonna be bulletproof
and retroactive.

1332
06:03:33,278 --> 06:03:35,007
Because Marty's too nice to say it...

1333
06:03:35,180 --> 06:03:38,980
...but with all you know about this place,
the clients and people who work here...

1334
06:03:39,151 --> 06:03:41,711
...it makes it a little weird
when you ask for 80 grand.

1335
06:03:42,387 --> 06:03:45,083
If I was gonna shake anybody down,
I'd come to you...

1336
06:03:45,257 --> 06:03:47,919
...and it wouldn't be for 80 grand.
Is this him or you?

1337
06:03:48,093 --> 06:03:50,687
- Lf I'm wrong, I apologize.
- You're way the fuck wrong.

1338
06:03:50,862 --> 06:03:52,090
So there you go.

1339
06:03:52,264 --> 06:03:53,925
Enough. Okay? Everybody.

1340
06:03:54,800 --> 06:03:56,961
He's an asshole, but he knows it.

1341
06:03:57,369 --> 06:04:00,634
And you're on the record.
Okay? Everybody happy?

1342
06:04:01,273 --> 06:04:03,969
JEAN: Don Jeffries is here.
- We're on the way.

1343
06:04:04,776 --> 06:04:08,872
Call Bob Nast.
Just see if they need help with this thing.

1344
06:04:12,451 --> 06:04:13,816
You're welcome.

1345
06:05:06,705 --> 06:05:09,071
You said 12. This is 75.

1346
06:05:09,241 --> 06:05:11,402
Well, don't get too excited.
You want a drink?

1347
06:05:11,576 --> 06:05:13,441
No. I'm working.

1348
06:05:15,881 --> 06:05:19,408
So we're square, then. No bad blood.

1349
06:05:19,584 --> 06:05:21,279
You're just doing your job.

1350
06:05:21,453 --> 06:05:22,920
That's right.

1351
06:05:23,855 --> 06:05:25,584
Take it easy, Gabe.

1352
06:05:26,591 --> 06:05:27,956
Michael.

1353
06:05:39,705 --> 06:05:41,138
MAN 1:
<i>Check.</i>

1354
06:05:42,974 --> 06:05:44,236
MICHAEL:
<i>Check.</i>

1355
06:05:44,576 --> 06:05:47,306
- Check.
MAN 2: Half the pot. Two hundred.

1356
06:05:47,479 --> 06:05:48,776
Two hundred to go.

1357
06:06:26,151 --> 06:06:27,914
So, what happened with the bar?

1358
06:06:28,086 --> 06:06:30,111
You just had to be a rock star, huh?

1359
06:06:37,729 --> 06:06:39,993
[PHONE RINGING]

1360
06:06:52,611 --> 06:06:55,375
What are you doing? You just got here.

1361
06:06:55,547 --> 06:06:57,481
Guy plays nine hands, walks away.

1362
06:06:57,649 --> 06:07:01,813
I scare you away? What did I do?
Did I scare you away?

1363
06:07:37,589 --> 06:07:38,647
Get out.

1364
06:07:40,025 --> 06:07:42,152
<i>Get out of the car now.</i>

1365
06:07:43,895 --> 06:07:44,884
- Walter?
MAN: <i>Michael.</i>

1366
06:07:45,063 --> 06:07:47,258
<i>- Michael. Thank God you're there.</i>
- Yeah.

1367
06:07:51,670 --> 06:07:53,604
You have eight...

1368
06:07:54,506 --> 06:07:57,236
<i>... six, five...</i>

1369
06:07:57,409 --> 06:07:59,741
<i>... four, three...</i>

1370
06:07:59,911 --> 06:08:01,538
<i>Get out of the car.</i>

1371
06:08:04,983 --> 06:08:08,009
MICHAEL: Tell him to stay off the phone.
MAN: <i>All right. But you're on it?</i>

1372
06:08:08,620 --> 06:08:10,053
Am I clean?

1373
06:08:10,222 --> 06:08:11,450
Just keep walking.

1374
06:08:11,623 --> 06:08:13,853
You copy. Am I clean?

1375
06:08:14,059 --> 06:08:17,051
Just keep moving.
He's walking to the car.

1376
06:08:17,596 --> 06:08:21,157
MAN: <i>... to let him know you're on the way.</i>
<i>I'll get back to you with the details.</i>

1377
06:08:21,333 --> 06:08:23,767
<i>- Just give me two minutes.</i>
- I'll be in the car.

1378
06:08:27,472 --> 06:08:30,908
IKER:
<i>I didn't finish. It's in, but I don't know.</i>

1379
06:08:59,070 --> 06:09:02,631
It's loose. I got a pulse.
He's up there somewhere, but...

1380
06:09:04,409 --> 06:09:06,343
Let's find a way to boost the signal.

1381
06:09:13,919 --> 06:09:15,819
MICHAEL:
I don't know what Walter promised you...

1382
06:09:15,987 --> 06:09:17,113
GREER:
A miracle worker!

1383
06:09:17,289 --> 06:09:20,520
That's Walter on the phone,
20 minutes ago. Direct quote, okay?

1384
06:09:20,692 --> 06:09:22,523
"I'm sending you a miracle worker."

1385
06:09:22,694 --> 06:09:24,355
- Well, he misspoke.
- About what?

1386
06:09:24,529 --> 06:09:28,056
About the fact that you're the firm's fixer?
Or that you're any good at it?

1387
06:09:33,838 --> 06:09:35,772
We're up. Just got a signal.

1388
06:09:59,631 --> 06:10:01,997
VERNE: There's nothing back this way.
What's he doing?

1389
06:10:02,167 --> 06:10:03,361
IKER:
Maybe he's lost.

1390
06:10:03,535 --> 06:10:05,332
VERNE: Wait a minute.
IKER: That's him.

1391
06:10:08,673 --> 06:10:09,901
He was alone, right?

1392
06:10:10,075 --> 06:10:12,873
- Yeah, I think so.
- Call it, yes or no?

1393
06:10:15,313 --> 06:10:16,940
We gotta turn around.

1394
06:10:47,178 --> 06:10:48,805
Talk to me.

1395
06:10:48,980 --> 06:10:50,538
It's strobing.

1396
06:10:50,715 --> 06:10:53,115
No, we're good. I think we're good.
Just keep going.

1397
06:11:08,933 --> 06:11:10,525
No, he turned. Somehow he turned.

1398
06:11:10,702 --> 06:11:12,067
- Where?
- He took...

1399
06:11:12,570 --> 06:11:14,538
- He took a left.
- I don't have a left.

1400
06:11:24,516 --> 06:11:27,451
- East. He's southeast.
- What, so we missed it?

1401
06:11:27,619 --> 06:11:29,746
- Or the grid is wrong.
- Hang on.

1402
06:11:39,931 --> 06:11:42,627
- We gotta go back to one.
- One is what? Where's our one?

1403
06:11:42,834 --> 06:11:45,826
Half a mile straight ahead.
Just keep driving. Just go.

1404
06:11:52,710 --> 06:11:55,338
It says we're closing.
But that's west. It can't be west.

1405
06:11:55,513 --> 06:11:56,571
The signal or the grid?

1406
06:11:56,748 --> 06:11:59,478
- It's both. It just keeps dropping out.
- Goddamn it.

1407
06:12:50,702 --> 06:12:52,169
Give me the cell.

1408
06:12:54,706 --> 06:12:56,401
Our signal's good.

1409
06:12:59,811 --> 06:13:01,802
[EXPLOSION]

1410
06:14:34,305 --> 06:14:35,567
What?

1411
06:14:38,209 --> 06:14:39,904
Thanks, Mickey.

1412
06:14:40,078 --> 06:14:41,739
Just get me out of here.

1413
06:14:49,454 --> 06:14:53,185
I wanna get a meeting scheduled on this,
soon as we can. Thursday at the latest.

1414
06:14:53,358 --> 06:14:55,724
I think we should have someone from
the equity group there.

1415
06:14:55,893 --> 06:14:56,985
- Jeff.
- Maybe McDonnell...

1416
06:14:57,161 --> 06:14:58,651
- Yeah?
- Did you hear?

1417
06:14:58,830 --> 06:15:01,355
- Yeah, yeah. They closed U/North.
MAN: No. Michael Clayton.

1418
06:15:01,799 --> 06:15:02,857
What?

1419
06:15:03,034 --> 06:15:05,935
Car bomb. Upstate. This morning.
He was killed.

1420
06:15:06,971 --> 06:15:07,995
What?

1421
06:15:09,674 --> 06:15:11,505
Holy shit.

1422
06:15:25,690 --> 06:15:30,627
KAREN: <i>It has been and it remains</i>
<i>the U/North position...</i>

1423
06:15:30,795 --> 06:15:34,891
<i>... that this lawsuit is baseless</i>
<i>and without merit.</i>

1424
06:15:35,066 --> 06:15:39,127
Our reluctance to negotiate
was anchored by this belief...

1425
06:15:39,304 --> 06:15:44,469
...and reinforced by the plaintiffs' demand
for settlement...

1426
06:15:44,642 --> 06:15:47,202
...in excess of 3 billion dollars.

1427
06:15:47,378 --> 06:15:50,836
The reason that we are
all here today is...

1428
06:15:51,015 --> 06:15:54,883
...that several key elements
in the case have changed.

1429
06:15:55,887 --> 06:16:00,324
<i>You all have</i>
<i>a tentative proposal packet...</i>

1430
06:16:00,925 --> 06:16:04,884
<i>... which outlines the details,</i>
<i>but the bottom line is this:</i>

1431
06:16:05,063 --> 06:16:07,827
<i>Over the past several months</i>
<i>we had gotten word...</i>

1432
06:16:07,999 --> 06:16:11,332
...that the plaintiffs were
growing impatient...

1433
06:16:11,502 --> 06:16:15,336
...and were in the process
of revising their settlement numbers.

1434
06:16:15,840 --> 06:16:17,307
<i>We also learned...</i>

1435
06:16:17,475 --> 06:16:21,411
<i>... that the plaintiffs' attorneys' fees</i>
<i>were capped at 32 percent...</i>

1436
06:16:21,579 --> 06:16:23,672
<i>... up to 400 million dollars...</i>

1437
06:16:24,115 --> 06:16:28,347
...above which,
their fees dropped to 24 percent.

1438
06:16:28,519 --> 06:16:33,081
So we knew that there would be
this motivational dead zone for them...

1439
06:16:33,257 --> 06:16:34,588
...in the middle there.

1440
06:16:35,360 --> 06:16:37,055
<i>Finally...</i>

1441
06:16:37,228 --> 06:16:41,562
...our finance team informed us
that they had run the numbers...

1442
06:16:41,733 --> 06:16:43,564
...and that the tax benefit...

1443
06:16:43,735 --> 06:16:46,966
...provided that we bring
the settlement in under 600 million...

1444
06:16:47,138 --> 06:16:49,572
...and within this fiscal year...

1445
06:16:49,741 --> 06:16:55,611
...that the write-off on this settlement
would essentially pay for itself.

1446
06:16:56,114 --> 06:17:00,312
<i>The package that you have before you</i>
<i>represents, in my judgment...</i>

1447
06:17:00,752 --> 06:17:05,553
<i>... the strongest possible position for</i>
<i>our company under the circumstances.</i>

1448
06:17:05,723 --> 06:17:07,418
<i>And, as chief counsel...</i>

1449
06:17:07,592 --> 06:17:10,857
...it is my recommendation
that this proposal be confirmed.

1450
06:17:11,929 --> 06:17:15,456
Thank you, Karen. If you just give us
a few minutes to talk about it.

1451
06:17:15,633 --> 06:17:17,897
Certainly. I'll be right outside.

1452
06:17:20,304 --> 06:17:21,293
Well...

1453
06:17:44,429 --> 06:17:46,260
How'd it go in there?

1454
06:17:49,300 --> 06:17:51,495
Pretty freaky, huh?

1455
06:17:51,669 --> 06:17:54,638
Did you see Arthur?
He's wandering around here somewhere.

1456
06:17:57,175 --> 06:18:00,440
I'm kidding. Lighten up.

1457
06:18:02,013 --> 06:18:05,710
You got one of these? It's a great memo.
It's an oldie but a goodie.

1458
06:18:08,886 --> 06:18:10,353
Got your heart racing, don't I?

1459
06:18:10,521 --> 06:18:12,648
I don't know what it is
you think you're doing.

1460
06:18:12,824 --> 06:18:14,189
What do you think I'm doing?

1461
06:18:14,358 --> 06:18:16,155
The suit's over. We have a deal.

1462
06:18:16,327 --> 06:18:19,023
Whatever that is,
it's meaningless at this point.

1463
06:18:19,197 --> 06:18:22,860
You think? I must have gotten it wrong.
I thought you had a tentative proposal.

1464
06:18:23,034 --> 06:18:25,229
I didn't realize you'd signed
all those checks.

1465
06:18:25,403 --> 06:18:28,702
That's a drag. I got a thousand of these.
What am I gonna do with them?

1466
06:18:28,873 --> 06:18:30,204
I'm calling Marty.

1467
06:18:30,374 --> 06:18:32,740
Good. Good. Do it.
That's a great place to start.

1468
06:18:32,910 --> 06:18:35,708
Let's find out who told him
Arthur was calling Anna Kysersun.

1469
06:18:35,880 --> 06:18:37,711
Let's find out who tapped those phones.

1470
06:18:37,882 --> 06:18:41,682
This memorandum, even if it's authentic,
which I doubt, I highly doubt...

1471
06:18:41,853 --> 06:18:45,289
- I know what you did to Arthur.
- It's protected. It belongs to U/North.

1472
06:18:45,456 --> 06:18:48,220
- I know you killed him.
- It's attorney-client privilege.

1473
06:18:48,392 --> 06:18:52,055
See, now, that's just not
the way to go here, Karen.

1474
06:18:52,230 --> 06:18:54,926
For such a smart person,
you really are lost, aren't you?

1475
06:18:55,099 --> 06:18:56,430
This conversation is over.

1476
06:18:56,601 --> 06:19:00,037
I'm not the guy that you kill.
I'm the guy that you buy.

1477
06:19:00,204 --> 06:19:02,729
Are you so fucking blind
you don't even see what I am?

1478
06:19:02,907 --> 06:19:06,399
I'm the easiest part of your whole
goddamn problem and you're gonna kill me?

1479
06:19:06,711 --> 06:19:09,839
Don't you know who I am?
I'm a fixer. I'm a bagman.

1480
06:19:10,014 --> 06:19:13,415
I do everything from shoplifting housewives
to bent congressmen...

1481
06:19:13,584 --> 06:19:15,484
...and you're gonna kill me?

1482
06:19:16,420 --> 06:19:19,253
What do you need, Karen? Lay it on me.

1483
06:19:19,423 --> 06:19:23,120
You want a carry permit? You want
a heads-up on an insider-trading subpoena?

1484
06:19:23,294 --> 06:19:27,128
I sold out Arthur for 80 grand
and a contract and you're gonna kill me?

1485
06:19:28,633 --> 06:19:30,066
What do you want?

1486
06:19:30,234 --> 06:19:31,758
What do I want?

1487
06:19:31,936 --> 06:19:33,528
I want more.

1488
06:19:34,038 --> 06:19:35,801
I want out.

1489
06:19:35,973 --> 06:19:38,601
And with this, I want everything.

1490
06:19:40,378 --> 06:19:41,606
Is there a number?

1491
06:19:41,779 --> 06:19:43,371
Ten is a number.

1492
06:19:43,548 --> 06:19:45,573
Ten? Ten what?

1493
06:19:47,618 --> 06:19:49,108
Ten million?

1494
06:19:49,287 --> 06:19:52,723
Where do you think I'm gonna get
10 million dollars?

1495
06:19:53,291 --> 06:19:55,191
You know what's great about this?

1496
06:19:55,359 --> 06:19:57,657
Did you read it to the end?
You see who signed it?

1497
06:19:58,229 --> 06:20:00,129
Let's go in and ask Don Jeffries...

1498
06:20:00,298 --> 06:20:03,290
...if he wants to pass the hat
for a worthy cause.

1499
06:20:05,136 --> 06:20:07,536
This would have to be
a longer conversation...

1500
06:20:07,705 --> 06:20:09,832
...and would have to take place
somewhere else.

1501
06:20:10,007 --> 06:20:11,497
Where? My car?

1502
06:20:13,077 --> 06:20:14,101
All right.

1503
06:20:15,279 --> 06:20:18,305
I'm gonna make it easy. Let's make it 5.

1504
06:20:18,482 --> 06:20:20,279
Five and I'll forget about Arthur.

1505
06:20:22,653 --> 06:20:27,420
Five is easier. Yeah, 5 is something
that we could talk about.

1506
06:20:27,592 --> 06:20:31,323
Good. And then the other 5 is
to forget about the 468 people...

1507
06:20:31,495 --> 06:20:33,588
...that you knocked off
with your weed killer.

1508
06:20:33,764 --> 06:20:36,130
Let me finish up this meeting.
I'll talk to Don...

1509
06:20:36,300 --> 06:20:38,894
Do I look like I'm negotiating?!

1510
06:20:39,070 --> 06:20:40,401
DON:
Karen?

1511
06:20:41,105 --> 06:20:42,970
KAREN: One second.
- Everything okay?

1512
06:20:44,342 --> 06:20:45,331
Yes.

1513
06:20:46,344 --> 06:20:50,144
Ten million dollars. Bank of my choosing.
Offshore. Immediately.

1514
06:20:50,314 --> 06:20:51,440
- Yes.
- Say it!

1515
06:20:51,616 --> 06:20:55,484
Ten million dollars, your account,
the moment this meeting is through.

1516
06:20:55,653 --> 06:20:57,951
DON: Karen! Everyone's waiting.
KAREN: I'm coming, Don.

1517
06:20:58,990 --> 06:21:00,355
You have a deal.

1518
06:21:00,925 --> 06:21:02,187
You're so fucked.

1519
06:21:02,526 --> 06:21:03,857
What?

1520
06:21:04,362 --> 06:21:06,227
- You're fucked.
- What do you mean?

1521
06:21:06,397 --> 06:21:08,627
- Take a wild guess.
DON: Is there a problem?

1522
06:21:08,799 --> 06:21:11,495
- I don't understand.
- Let me get a picture while I'm at it.

1523
06:21:11,669 --> 06:21:14,467
- You don't want the money?
- Keep the money. You'll need it.

1524
06:21:14,639 --> 06:21:16,231
Is this fellow bothering you?

1525
06:21:16,407 --> 06:21:17,635
Am I bothering you?

1526
06:21:17,808 --> 06:21:21,835
DON: Karen, I've got a board waiting in there.
What the hell's going on? Who are you?

1527
06:21:22,013 --> 06:21:23,708
I'm Shiva, the god of death.

1528
06:21:23,881 --> 06:21:27,510
DON: Ron! Ronny, I need security
out here immediately.

1529
06:21:28,419 --> 06:21:29,681
All right. Here we go.

1530
06:21:29,854 --> 06:21:33,051
That guy right there, stop him.
Grab that guy.

1531
06:21:34,659 --> 06:21:35,853
What are you doing?

1532
06:21:36,027 --> 06:21:37,756
DALBERTO:
We're detectives with the N.Y.P.D.

1533
06:21:37,928 --> 06:21:39,896
Come back with us
and we'll explain everything.

1534
06:21:40,064 --> 06:21:43,329
Check on her. Make sure she doesn't need
any medical attention.

1535
06:21:43,501 --> 06:21:45,662
You guys go into the ballroom.
Nobody leaves.

1536
06:21:45,836 --> 06:21:47,599
Have your guys cover every exit.

1537
06:21:47,772 --> 06:21:50,570
DON: Will you please explain to me
what's going on here?

1538
06:21:51,208 --> 06:21:52,573
Did you get all that?

1539
06:21:52,743 --> 06:21:54,938
Yeah. Got it.

1540
06:21:58,582 --> 06:22:01,415
- You okay?
- Yeah. Just gotta get some air.

1541
06:22:01,585 --> 06:22:03,075
Sure.

1542
06:22:03,454 --> 06:22:06,218
Just stay close, okay?

1543
06:22:06,390 --> 06:22:07,618
Okay.

1544
06:23:18,262 --> 06:23:20,093
DRIVER:
So, what are we doing?

1545
06:23:27,171 --> 06:23:29,162
Give me 50 dollars' worth.

1546
06:23:31,041 --> 06:23:32,702
Just drive.

1547
06:29:17,955 --> 06:29:19,946
[ENGLISH SDH]

